      "id": "node-1772568235171-copy-1772597026894-copy-1772597665391-copy-1772634223938-copy-1772636135428",
      "type": "conversation",
      "display_position": {
        "x": -547.6213139922562,
        "y": -40.64093601258009
      },
      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask for the best phone number to reach the user.\n\nSay something like: \"What's the best phone number to reach you?\"\n\nIf the user says \"use this number\" or \"you already have it\", respond:\n\"Got it, we'll use the number you're calling from.\"\n\nA valid US phone number has exactly 10 digits (or 11 with country code).\n\nWhen the user provides a number:\n- A valid US phone number has exactly 10 digits (or 11 with country code).\n- Always read the number back to confirm. For example: \n  \"Just to make sure I have it right — that's (785) 390-9750, correct?\"\n- If the user says it's wrong, ask them to repeat it slowly.\n- If the number sounds too short or too long, say:\n  \"Hmm, that doesn't sound quite right — could you say it one more time?\"\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Ask user's name and dob",
      "edges": [
