      "id": "node-1772570870418-copy-1772597026894-copy-1772597665391-copy-1772634223938-copy-1772636135428",
      "type": "conversation",
      "display_position": {
        "x": -1425.7600339646906,
        "y": -20.204065895133528
      },
      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Collect the user's first name, last name and date of birth.\n\nSay something like: \"I'd be happy to help you schedule an appointment! \nCan I get your full name and date of birth?\"\n\nIf the user provides only their first name and last name, ask for their date of birth.\nIf the user provides only their date of birth, ask for their first and last name.\n\nIf the user is hesitant or refuses:\n- Reassure them: \"No worries, we just need that to look up your record \n  or create one for you.\"\n- If they still decline, say: \"That's okay, we can get that when you \n  come in. Let me continue with the other details.\"\n\nDo NOT ask more than twice for information the user has declined to provide."
      }
    },
